### User-scoped memory

Give each user their own memory file. The agent remembers preferences, context, and history per user while core agent instructions stay fixed. Users can also have per-user [skills](/oss/deepagents/skills) if stored in a user-scoped backend.

The namespace uses `(user_id,)` so each user gets an isolated copy of the memory file. User A's preferences never leak into User B's conversations.

:::python
```python
from deepagents import create_deep_agent
from deepagents.backends import CompositeBackend, StateBackend, StoreBackend

agent = create_deep_agent(
    model="google_genai:gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
    memory=["/memories/preferences.md"],
    skills=["/skills/"],
    backend=CompositeBackend(
        default=StateBackend(),
        routes={
            "/memories/": StoreBackend(
                namespace=lambda rt: (rt.server_info.user.identity,),
            ),
            "/skills/": StoreBackend(
                namespace=lambda rt: (rt.server_info.user.identity,),
            ),
        },
    ),
)
```
